Author: Akhil Lendale
Body: Simply fast

The first genuine Chrome replacement? With Google twiddling their thumbs on adding a proper reader mode to Chrome and with reader mode such a necessity for internet browsers these days, I'm happy to report that this app implements a reader mode feature very well indeed. The app also has a clean interface with a wealth of useful options. Only one glaring bug has been found so far: on my Lenovo Yoga Tab 10, selecting desktop as the user agent makes Google search results show up as garbeled text (probably basic HTML), thus not rendering the page correctly. The reader mode, while good, could also use some tweaks. For example, the web article I tested showed up as a single large block of text, which originally had paragraphs for the actual page's content. I hope the browser continues to be updated and improved then it will surely get 5 stars. A fantastic browser for Android.

Author: Theo Moolenaar
Body: Overall a great browser. I love how it's simple and clean in design yet far more customisable than most browsers. A few things, however, need attention. Firstly, I would like to see the ability to open new tabs in the background (perhaps have a toggle for this in settings). Secondly, Incognito doesn't really work properly. If I open an incognito tab then I can no longer access my other tabs and any other tabs I open are automatically also incognito tabs. Also, if I minimise the app and then re-open it using the shortcut, my incognito "window" and all its tabs disappear and my normal tabs reappear. This is highly impractical and unintuitive.  If anything, since Lollipop introduced the capability to have multiple windows per app (Chrome used to make use of this), at least have Incognito open in a separate window so that it is possible to switch between normal and incognito browsing.

Author: Aleksandar Dimitric
Body: This is the best Android browser I've ever used. It is extremely light and fast (even on my Galaxy smartphone from 2011), bookmarks are so easy to reach and it looks really functional and minimal with its great fullscreen mode and black AMOLED theme. My favourite feature is the "Inverted Grayscale" rendering mode- it transforms my AMOLED smartphone to an e-book reader saving battery. Then there is an option to set any user agent, activate text reflow and change the text size of any web page. I really can't believe all these features are able to fit in only 2MB (Chrome was taking more than 100MB on my phone, bloating more and more and being incredibly slow to start and browse on my Galaxy S II). I'm happy to recommend this browser to anyone. I bought the "Lightning Web Browser +"  that also has an option to block ads, but I wanted to leave a review here as well since I really love this app.

In the future I'd still like to see support for auto form fills and the ability to open new tabs in background. Other than that the browser is perfect for me.

Author: Jerry
Body: I loved the fact that this app had some great features with an itty bitty footprint, BUT customizing things like where to download items is pretty behind the curve. In many droid devices the "device storage" is divided in half and one of those halves is referred to as SDCARD0 (that is a zero), and that is where this browser will only store downloads --when, usually, we want to store those items on the little card we took the time to purchase, pay for and shove in that slot of our phones so that we can store "things" like downloaded files to it. I was just about to buy the pro version. If anyone knows if the pro version actually allows customization... well I guess the developers are the only ones who can answer that question here.

Subject: Lightning = solid + fast
Body: I do not know any more how many browsers I tried ... endless. I keep on comng back to Lightning. Compared, the small size, number of (relevant!) functions, speed, memory foot-print, and ease of operation, Lightning is to my opinion still the best browser out there. It functions stabil and renders most pages nicely. Another plus, it shows lesser advertisements than the more modern Chromium based browsers, in particular lesser intrusive ads. The few banners slipping through with Lightning are ok for me. I very much pity more and more websites show some message such as "your browser is not anymore supported. Obviously they want to make me using salesware. Peter Kroll, Singapore

Body: バグが多い。クラッシュ頻度も高い。フリーズ時間が長い。(平均50秒〜100秒前後の間は操作不能となる。)  表示が崩れるサイトが多い。(ない方を探すのが大変。)他のブラウザでは正常に表示されるのでLightning系のみが抱える問題である。 手動で表示(ズーム)倍率を変更しても、一定時間経過後にはもとのサイズにリセットされるバグがある。 一部、Webページが表示されずにhtmlソースがそのまま表示されるサイトがある。  本家Lightningが駄目なら、他のLightning系エンジンのブラウザも同様の欠陥を抱えているということ。  ニュース系サイトでズームアウトが出来ないものが多い。 (表示エンジンに不都合があるということ。) ブックマークはフォルダ別には出来ない。(機能的には20年前のPCブラウザ以下)

Author: kz kz
Body: 戻る再読込の有効無効、リソース割り込み（広告カット）が出来る機能をご検討下さい。これは、 Webページ上の埋め込みリソース(画像やJavaScript、インラインフレームなど)のURLが条件に一致する場合、サーバからの取得を中止してダミーの画像やテキストにすり替えるという機能で、「Opera Mobile」などにあるコンテンツブロックのようなもの。 不要なデータの読み込みを防止することで、ページの表示速度を向上させたり、メモリ消費・CPU負荷を軽減するなどの効果が期待できる。回線速度やマシンパワーの限られたモバイル端末では特に嬉しい機能。

Body: If speed is your only concern, I recommend it. But for me it needs a night mode button that invert all but the images (see Pyrope browser) and a exception list to add sites where this mode will never apply. This mode is currently burried in settings. The desktop mode button status should change accordingly to currently used mode. And improve Bookmark folder creation and management. Finally, add a go to top button at the bottom of the page like many browsers do or make the scrollbar draggable. Else it is very fast indeed.

Subject: Great but...
Body: This is very good on old Android phones like mine, but there are some key features that I miss, including : - Long press on a link to open in a new tab (or other options) - Smart address bar, for searching in google directly with the address bar - Private browsing - When there are multiple tabs, change the size of the tabs so that they are all on the screen - Smart fullscreen (smart hiding of the address bar) With these features, it would be the perfect browser for my slow HTC Desire.

En bref il ne manque juste que l'apparition/disparition intelligente de la barre de recherche. Je conseille !

Author: Luca Furlotti
Body: Leggerissimo e molto veloce. Open source. Però ha diversi bug e viene aggiornato una volta ogni qualche mese. L'ultimo aggiornamento, poi, non ha risolto i problemi storici (la gestione rudimentale dei preferiti, la tastiera che va a nascondere ciò che si sta scrivendo, le frecce avanti/indietro scomode..), invece ne ha creati di nuovi (la metà inferiore dello schermo che ogni tanto diventa tutta grigia finché non si riavvia l'app). Poi ok la leggerezza, ma mancano alcune funzioni essenziali come il force zoom e il desktop mode. L'ad blocker c'è ma non è molto efficace. E' un browser che meriterebbe,ma così com'è ora la sconsiglio.

margini per crescere ci sono ma va benissimo è poi non da poco solo  autorizzazioni necessarie consigliatissimo. altri browser sono d'interfaccia migliore ma ti chiedono tutte le autorizzazioni possibili

Author: Christian Onzaca
Subject: Davvero interessante
Body: Un browser che mi ha stupito davvero tanto, ma va ancora migliorato, a cominciare dalla traduzione (3/4 dell'interfaccia sono inglesi). Bisognerebbe poi introdurre uno switch per la desktop mode, ottimizzare le prestazioni e i consumi (consuma parecchie risorse tra batteria e RAM) e migliorare la home page. È presente un fastidioso bug nella casella per l'URL (provare a cliccarci sopra e a cancellare tutto), un altro che sposta la pagina quando faccio doppio tap. Confido nel lavoro dello sviluppatore.

I contro di questo browser sono i tab limitati a solo 5, molto problematico per un' utilizzo odierno, e un generale rallentamento sulla gestione del plug in flash e la sola mono lingua inglese che stona su un sistema di lingua differente.

Un piccolo bug è quello del campo dell'indirizzo: infatti se cliccate una volta sopra non seleziona tutto il link. Per il resto app fatta bene. Sconsigliata se usata come app di default.

War mal perfekt! Unter Android 7 Nougat ist auch Lightning 4.4.2 quasi nicht mehr zu gebrauchen. Habe auf dem Huawei Mate 9 extreme Probleme mit dem Zertifikatsmanagment. Viele https Seiten werden als unsicher eingestuft und erst nach vielfacher Bestätigung geladen. Abschalten der Sicherheitsmeldungen ebenfalls nicht möglich. Lieber Entwickler, mach bitte was, daß es wieder geht! Danke!

Other apps and browsers work perfectly fine with SwiftKey. Seems the development of this app has stopped. Loved it in the past. Automatic ad loading is annoying as hell and you can't stop it. Comes again and again. Intentional to get money? A no go as not all ads are serious. Switched to Opera Mini. Android 6.0.1

Author: Martin Meis
Subject: Super Browser
Body: Lightning ist aktuell mein absoluter Lieblingsbrowser für Android. Er hat so wunderschöne Einstellmöglichkeiten wie das automatische Löschen von Cookies und Verlauf, ist schnell und man kann die Standardsuchmaschine selber definieren. Super ist auch der Schnellzugriff auf Links und Tabs per Wischgeste. Für mich ein absolut vorbildlicher Browser. Den fünften Stern hab ich aufgehoben, weil er noch keine AddOns unterstützt.

Ständige freezes beim suchen mit Google oder Eingabe einer linkadr.  Verwendet man einen Link über ein andere App,  startet Lightning mit leerem Tab. Schade drum. Bei mir wird der Browser nun gelöscht, da das ständige einfrieren mehr als störend ist. Das Problem wurde schon öfter abgesprochen, Reaktion in Form einen Update = 0

Subject: Spitzenklasse unter allen Browsern

Videos bisher alle abspielbar. Keine Werbung. Sehr gut durchdachte Bedienelemente. Lesezeichenleiste da wo sie hingehört. Habe ca. 20 Browser ausprobiert. Das ist der, der immer genutzt wird. @Developer: Thanks, many many thanks for this stress-free user experience.

Subject: Super snappy
Body: I'm coming from Chrome, after the last update messed up everything. Lightning is definitely infinite times faster, complex sites scroll buttery smooth and the UI is uncluttered/minimalistic and makes sense. I like the sidebars. Missing: - left sidebar should be bottom-aligned so one can easier reach the tabs, including new tab; - button to close all tabs; - (bookmark) sync with chrome/others; - can't find normal tabs when in incognito mode (did i oversee them?) I really appreciate your work, Thanks!

Author: Rodrigo Alves de Carvalho
Body: Excelente. Simples Assim. Simplesmente o melhor!

Testei quase toda lista de browsers, em busca de algum que tivesse ajuste/quebra de texto para facilitar a leitura, pra não ser obrigado a usar os famosões que roubam quase 300mb da sua memória ram e ainda te enchem de lixo de novelas e pseudo celebridades.  E encontrei este minúsculo e fantástico browser que merece as 5 estrelas e parabéns ao desenvolvedor.   Não é perfeito, tem seus probleminhas, falta adblock para transitar um pouco mais rápido, precisa de mais abas para home de favoritos, a quebra de texto não funciona em um forum que leio e faz falta.  Mas nada disso tira seus méritos extraordinários de simplicidade e eficiência em tão pouco tamanho.   Espero que ele evolua e seja reconhecido.

Author: Петр Шеремет
Subject: Sehr gut
Body: Милый сердцу опенсорсовский минимализм :). Но пользоваться удобнно. Я аж удивился. Сейчас  провел тест в условиях низкоскоростной GPRS сети: главную страницу яндекса Lightning открыл почти вдвое быстрее, чем Опера Мини 7.5.33361 (16 сек. против почти 34) - чем немало озадачил.  Забираю в тестовую эксплуатацию:)  Пока что ставлю 4.  ЗЫ. Но вот от прикрученного плагина к Next браузеру с сохранением страницы в pdf  я бы не отказался. Или от отдельного :) Сутки спустя. Увы - сглазил: на вторые сутки использования браузер начал вылетать после завершения ввода теста в ландшафтной ориентации тушки. Т.е. делаем поисковый запрос, открывается страница результатов и тут же программа рушится. Остерегусь хаять софтину, возможно это конфликт между софтом и железом (Lenovo A369i, прошивка ROW S110, root, TWRP 2.6.3) А жаль :( Браузер мне понравился.

Author: Mario
Subject: Entre el montón de APP mediocres que sólo buscan explotar datos del usuario, un navegador destacable en Android
Body: Usa el mismo motor de Chrome y Opera, así que las diferencias en seguridad no deberían ser abismales. Por compartir motor, ocupa casi los mismos recursos de CPU y RAM; pero tiene como ventaja lo poco que ocupa la APP. En cuanto al uso, las barras deslizantes e interfaz simplificada hacen que este navegador aparente ser más rápido. El reflujo de texto es muy bueno y tiene las opciones adecuadas para convertirse en tu navegador diario.

Y ésta es la razón por la que lo desinstalé. - Algunas páginas de video no las carga bien, y en lugar de reproducir el video, solo carga una preimagen del mismo.  ****************************  It is very light, the more light that I could try. But it has two problems: - It have conflict with Voice Search. Using voice search, the results can not be displayed in the browser and an error occurs. And this is the reason that I uninstalled. - Some video pages do not load well, and instead of playing the video, uploading a pre-image of it.
